name: FL Health Collier
tweet: When cooking for #Thanksgiving it's important to practice #foodsafety.   Wash your hands for 20 seconds.   Cook all food to the proper temperature.   Refrigerate perishable food within 2 hours. If the temperature is above 90 degrees Fahrenheit, chill food within 1 hour.  https://t.co/QbVlSC1Msi

tweet: When planning out your #Thanksgiving activities remember that COVID-19 is still in our community. tweet: Follow these healthy holiday habits!   Wash your hands with soap and water often.   Do not skip meals to save room for the feast.   Eat Slowly!
